# Applies to BOTH image builds (docker build context is always the ausmt repo root — see the
# CAVEAT comments in engine.Dockerfile / portal.Dockerfile). Keeps images lean and reproducible:
# dev-only tooling, caches, and VCS metadata never need to enter a build context.

.git
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
*.egg-info

# Portal dev-only test tooling (jsdom interaction tests, node_modules) — not part of the shipped
# static site; portal.Dockerfile COPYs portal/ wholesale, so exclude these explicitly rather than
# hand-listing every file that IS shipped.
portal/node_modules
portal/tests

# NOTE: deploy/docker/** is intentionally NOT ignored here — portal.Dockerfile's
# `COPY deploy/docker/caddy/Caddyfile ...` needs it present in the build context (the context is
# the repo root, per both Dockerfiles' header comments). Only the dev-noise paths above are excluded.
